correctness.rationale: Major factual, structural, and schema issues. (a) Missing multiplicity: the article reports multiple ALD IGZO processes (supercycle ratios 0:2:2, 2:2:2, 4:2:2; different PL/GI oxidants and even 200 °C for composition D), but only one process is extracted. (b) Process–device mismatch: supercycleDesign is 2:2:2 while deviceProperties (μ=9.9 cm2/Vs, SS=240 mV/dec) correspond to Dev. A (0:2:2 with H2O-PL). (c) Many values are fabricated/not traceable: pressure (0.1 mTorr), dosing/purge times (1 ms), flow rates (10 sccm/100 sccm), growthPerCycle (0.1 Å), nucleationPeriod (10 cycles), saturation (True), uniformity (5%), conformality (AR=10), optical properties (n, absorption coefficient, band gap), electrical film properties (Hall carrier density, mobility, resistivity), on/off ratio (1e6), threshold voltage (0 V), reactor name/manufacturer (“Not Found”), carrier/purge gas (N2). None are in the article. (d) Internal inconsistencies: GPC×cycles does not match film thickness (0.1 Å × 100 cycles = 1 nm vs listed 20 nm). (e) Incorrect entries: deviceStructure set to “bottom-gate top-contact” whereas the article uses bottom-gate bottom-contact (BGBC). Atomic ratio set to “1:1:1” contradicts reported XPS ratios (e.g., 0.3:1:1.4; 1:1:1.6; 2:1:1.8). Precursor listed as “In-Ga precursor” assigned to GaOx is ambiguous and not clearly mapped to compounds as in the paper (TEIn + In–Ga single precursor + DEZn). (f) Schema violations: plasmaPower is null (should be omitted or a valid object); absorptionCoefficient unit given as PER-CENTI-M, but the schema requires UNITLESS for the specified quantity kinds. Overall, the extraction is largely ungrounded and inconsistent. Properties to correct/review: supercycleDesign vs device metrics, deviceStructure, plasmaPower (remove/structure properly), absorptionCoefficient unit, all dosing/purge/flow/pressure/GPC/nucleation/saturation values, optical/electrical film properties, atomic ratios/compositions, carrier/purging gases, and add separate processes for 0:2:2, 2:2:2, 4:2:2 and the 200 °C case with correct PL/GI oxidants and corresponding device results.

completeness.rationale: The extraction is largely incomplete and contains many untraceable or incorrect values, plus schema issues. (1) Multiple processes missing: the article reports distinct IGZO ALD supercycle designs and temperatures (TEIn/In-Ga precursor/DEZn = 0:2:2, 2:2:2, 4:2:2 at 150 °C, and 2:2:2 at 200 °C for composition D). Only a single process (2:2:2 at 150 °C) is represented. Each composition (A, B, C, D) should be a separate process with its own supercycleDesign, temperature, and device metrics. (2) Untraceable/invented parameters: pressure (0.1 mTorr), dosing times (1 ms), purge times, flow rates (10 sccm/100 sccm), nucleation period (10 cycles), saturation=True, growth-per-cycle (0.1 Å) are not reported anywhere in the article. Carrier/purging gas set to N2 is also not stated. (3) Misrepresented supercycle: the article defines the supercycle in terms of TEIn/In-Ga precursor/DEZn; the extraction lists numberofSubcycles only as InOx/ZnO/GaOx = 2:2:2 and omits the 0:2:2 and 4:2:2 cases and the 200 °C variant. (4) Film composition wrong: atomicRatio is given as 1:1:1, whereas Table 1 reports A=0.3:1:1.4, B=1:1:1.6, C=2:1:1.8 (XPS). ElementalConcentration set to a single 20% value is not traceable. (5) Device properties mismatches: fieldEffectMobility is populated with 9.9 cm^2/V·s, which in the article is μ_sat for Dev. A (not μ_FE); thresholdVoltage 0 V and on/off ratio 1e6 are not reported; deviceStructure is listed as bottom-gate top-contact, but the article uses BGBC (bottom-gate bottom-contact). SS=240 mV/dec for Dev. A is correct but devices B, C, D and their metrics (e.g., μ_sat = 23.5 and 27.6 cm^2/V·s) are omitted. (6) Schema/format issues: plasmaPower is provided as null (should be omitted if not PEALD); placeholders like 'Not Found' for reactor/deliveryMethod violate the no-empty-value expectation; many required materialProperties (uniformity, conformality, roughness, density, optical and Hall data) are filled with invented numbers not present in the article. To improve, add separate process instances for A, B, C, and D with correct supercycle ratios and temperatures; populate precursors/co-reactant exactly as reported; provide only traceable values (e.g., film thickness 20 nm, substrate SiO2/Si); correct device structure and device metrics per device; remove or leave out fields not reported rather than inventing values; and fix schema violations (omit plasmaPower if not used).
